Class Caregiver

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.mdbook.User
      • com.example.mdbook.Caregiver

  • class Caregiver
extends User
    Extends User into the caregiver class. Adds an arraylist of patients. Provides methods for adding and removing patients.
    Version:
    0.0.1
    Author:
    Noah Burghardt

      • Caregiver

        public Caregiver(java.lang.String userID,
                 java.lang.String userPhone,
                 java.lang.String userEmail)
        Creates new Caregiver in same way as superclass User. Generates patientList as an empty ArrayList of strings (patient IDs)
        Parameters:
        userID - the unique user ID, as a string. This class does not check for uniqueness.
        userPhone - the phone number, as a string
        userEmail - the email address, as a string

    • Method Detail

      • addPatient

        public void addPatient(Patient patient)
        Adds patient to caregivers patient list.
        Parameters:
        patient - The patient to add.

      • removePatient

        public boolean removePatient(Patient patient)
        Removes patient from caregivers patient list. Patient isn't deleted but will be dereferenced if not saved to disk or cloud.
        Parameters:
        patient - The patient to remove.
        Returns:
        True on successful removal, false if patient couldn't be found.
